ðŸ–¥ï¸ ESSENTIAL TERMINAL COMMANDS FOR CSE STUDENTS (LINUX)
ðŸ”¹ 1. BASIC FILE & DIRECTORY COMMANDS (MOST IMPORTANT)
Command	Purpose
pwd	Show present working directory
ls	List files and directories
ls -l	Long listing with permissions
ls -a	Show hidden files
cd dirname	Change directory
cd ..	Move to parent directory
cd ~	Go to home directory
mkdir dir	Create directory
rmdir dir	Delete empty directory
rm file	Delete file
rm -r dir	Delete directory recursively
cp src dest	Copy file
cp -r dir1 dir2	Copy directory
mv old new	Rename / move file
ðŸ”¹ 2. FILE VIEWING & EDITING COMMANDS
Command	Purpose
cat file.c	Display file contents
cat > file.txt	Create file using terminal
less file.txt	View file page by page
more file.txt	View file (older)
head file.txt	First 10 lines
tail file.txt	Last 10 lines
nano file.c	Simple editor
vi file.c	Advanced editor
vim file.c	Improved vi editor
ðŸ”¹ 3. COMPILATION & PROGRAM EXECUTION (VERY IMPORTANT FOR LAB)
C Programs
gcc program.c
./a.out

gcc program.c -o prog
./prog

C++ Programs
g++ program.cpp
./a.out

Java Programs
javac Program.java
java Program

Python Programs
python3 program.py

ðŸ”¹ 4. FILE PERMISSIONS & OWNERSHIP (OS LAB VIVA FAVORITE)
Command	Purpose
chmod 777 file	Give all permissions
chmod 644 file	rw-r--r--
chmod +x file.sh	Make file executable
ls -l	View permissions
chown user file	Change owner
chgrp group file	Change group
ðŸ”¹ 5. PROCESS MANAGEMENT COMMANDS
Command	Purpose
ps	Show running processes
ps -ef	Detailed process list
top	Real-time process monitor
htop	Advanced process viewer
kill pid	Kill a process
kill -9 pid	Force kill
bg	Resume process in background
fg	Bring to foreground
ðŸ”¹ 6. SYSTEM INFORMATION COMMANDS
Command	Purpose
uname	System name
uname -a	Full system info
whoami	Current user
who	Logged-in users
date	Current date & time
cal	Calendar
df -h	Disk space
free -h	Memory usage
uptime	System running time
ðŸ”¹ 7. SEARCHING & FILTERING (IMPORTANT FOR DATA PROCESSING)
Command	Purpose
grep word file	Search word in file
grep -i word file	Case-insensitive
find . -name file	Search file
wc file	Word/line count
wc -l file	Line count
sort file	Sort file
uniq file	Remove duplicates
ðŸ”¹ 8. REDIRECTION & PIPES (OS LAB CORE TOPIC)
Command	Purpose
>	Output redirection
>>	Append output
<	Input redirection
`	`
Example:
ls > files.txt
cat file.txt | grep hello

ðŸ”¹ 9. NETWORKING COMMANDS (CSE + CN USEFUL)
Command	Purpose
ping google.com	Check connectivity
ifconfig	Network info
ip a	IP address
netstat	Network stats
ssh user@ip	Remote login
scp file user@ip:/path	File transfer
ðŸ”¹ 10. ARCHIVE & COMPRESSION COMMANDS
Command	Purpose
tar -cvf file.tar dir	Create archive
tar -xvf file.tar	Extract archive
zip file.zip file	Compress
unzip file.zip	Extract zip
gzip file	Compress
gunzip file.gz	Decompress
ðŸ”¹ 11. PACKAGE MANAGEMENT (VERY USEFUL)
Command	Purpose
sudo apt update	Update package list
sudo apt install gcc	Install package
sudo apt remove pkg	Remove package
sudo apt upgrade	Upgrade system
ðŸ”¹ 12. IPC & OS LAB RELATED COMMANDS
Command	Purpose
ipcs	View IPC resources
ipcrm	Remove IPC resource
strace ./a.out	Trace system calls
ltrace ./a.out	Trace library calls
ðŸ”¹ 13. SHELL & SHORTCUT COMMANDS (PRODUCTIVITY)
Shortcut	Purpose
Ctrl + C	Stop process
Ctrl + Z	Suspend process
Ctrl + L	Clear screen
clear	Clear terminal
history	Command history
!!	Run last command
exit	Exit terminal
